The parent has `max-height: 300px` with `overflow: hidden`, and the child has `max-height: 296px` with `overflow-y: auto`. The 4px difference accounts for the padding. This works, but is brittle -- if padding changes, the scroll behavior will break (either clipping content or showing a scrollbar on the parent). Consider using `max-height: 100%` on the child or deriving the value from the same token.

